Xi analysis

As inflation of p-values was observed in a previous analysis of baseline diagnosis on Xi, the model will now include surrogate variables.

In this case, surrogate variables have been generated using a model that only included disease status. This has generated 43 SVs, after the exclusion of 1 SVs which correlated with diagnosis.

Several models will be run, with an increasing number of SVs.

Packages used in this analysis: wateRmelon, dplyr, qqman, kableExtra, methylumi.
Results from this analysis are stored in "/mnt/data1/Janou/AddNeuroMed/XY analysis/Xi/Inflation correction/SVA".

The analysis was run using dasen normalised data, where covariates had been removed from male and female data, and Xi DNA methylation had been calculated.
